trend_summary: From earliest to latest image, built-up footprint expands gradually along main corridors. New housing fills forest gaps, commercial lots grow near highway junctions, and road network densifies. Green cover declines slightly but remains dominant. No high-rise cores emerge, confirming moderate, outward suburban growth.
notable_changes: Southern highway interchange upgraded to a full cloverleaf with extra ramps and wider pavement.
North-west industrial/business park extends northeastward, adding several large-roof buildings.
South-central forest cleared for a curvilinear residential subdivision with cul-de-sacs.
Central sports oval redeveloped, enlarging stands and parking areas.
